author: The Associated Press
title: Takeaways from internal documents on China's virus response
description: Top Chinese officials secretly determined they were likely facing an epidemic from a new coronavirus in mid-January, ordering preparations even as they downplayed it in public
content:
On Jan. 14, Chinas top health agency told provincial officials that they were facing a likely epidemic from a new coronavirus but didn't alert the public for six days.
